117 SECTION 4.
118 Said chapter is further amended by revising Code Section 30-4-2, relating to right to equal
119 public accommodations and right to be accompanied by guide dog or service dog, as follows:
120 "30-4-2.
121 (a) Physically or mentally impaired Blind persons, persons with visual disabilities, persons
122 with physical disabilities, and deaf persons are entitled to full and equal accommodations,
123 advantages, facilities, and privileges on all common carriers, airplanes, motor vehicles,
124 railroad trains, motor buses, streetcars, boats, or any other public conveyances or modes
125 of transportation and at hotels, lodging places, places of public accommodation,
126 amusement, or resort, and other places to which the general public is invited, subject only
127 to the conditions and limitations established by law and applicable alike to all persons.
128 (b)(1) Every totally or partially blind person shall have the right to be accompanied by
129 a guide dog, and every physically disabled person and every deaf physically or mentally
130 impaired person shall have the right to be accompanied by a service dog, especially
131 trained for the purpose, in any of the places listed in subsection (a) of this Code section
132 without being required to pay an extra charge for the guide or service dog; provided,
133 however, that he or she shall be liable for any damage done to the premises or facilities
134 by such service dog. In addition, if such totally or partially blind person, physically
135 disabled person, or deaf physically or mentally impaired person is a student at a private
136 or public school in this state, such person shall have the right to be accompanied by a
137 guide dog or service dog subject to liability for damage as provided in the preceding
138 sentence. The guide dog or service dog must be identified as having been trained by a
139 school for seeing eye, hearing, service, or guide dogs.
140 (2) Every person engaged in the training of a guide dog or service dog for the purpose
141 of accompanying a person as provided in paragraph (1) of this subsection shall have the
142 same right to be accompanied by such service dog being trained as the totally or partially
143 blind person, deaf person, or physically disabled physically or mentally impaired person
