184 accommodations, as follows:
185 "30-4-3.
186 (a) Physically or mentally impaired Blind persons, visually disabled persons, physically
187 disabled persons, and deaf persons shall be entitled to rent, lease, or purchase, as other
188 members of the general public, all housing accommodations offered for rent, lease, or other
189 compensation in this state, subject to the conditions and limitations established by law and
190 applicable alike to all persons.
191 (b) Every totally or partially blind person, every physically disabled person, and every deaf
192 physically or mentally impaired person who has a guide dog or service dog or who obtains
193 a guide dog or service dog and every person engaged in the training of a guide dog or
194 service dog shall be entitled to full and equal access to all housing accommodations
