203 SECTION 6.
204 Said chapter is further amended by revising Code Section 30-4-4, relating to denial of or
205 interference with admittance to or enjoyment of facilities or exercise of rights, as follows:
206 "30-4-4.
207 (a) Any person, firm, or corporation, or the agent of any person, firm, or corporation, who
208 denies or interferes with admittance to or enjoyment of the facilities enumerated in this
209 chapter or otherwise interferes with the rights of a totally or partially blind person,
210 physically disabled person, or deaf physically or mentally impaired person or person
211 engaged in the training or raising of a guide dog or service dog as provided by this chapter
212 shall be guilty of a misdemeanor of a high and aggravated nature and, upon conviction
213 thereof, shall be punished by a fine not to exceed $2,000.00, imprisonment confinement
214 for not more than 30 days, or both.
215 (b) Any individual who deliberately misrepresents himself or herself as qualified to use
216 a service dog or train or raise service dogs for the purpose of obtaining accommodations
217 or securing rights under this chapter shall be guilty of a misdemeanor of a high and
218 aggravated nature and, upon conviction thereof, shall be punished by a fine not to exceed
219 $2,000.00, confinement for not more than 30 days, or both."
